parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained cracking of the windshield can cause visibility issues, leading to accidents or injuries. The frequent replacement of windshields can also be a financial burden to the owner.
symptoms: The windshield cracks suddenly
often without any apparent impact or damage
in an "L" shape or straight line
starting from the top or center of the windshield and extending towards the driver's side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the brake pedal fails to respond
the engine revs up
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the driver takes their foot off the gas pedal
the vehicle accelerates independently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control fails to respond to the on/off reset button
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the engine revs up
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the driver takes their foot off the gas pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal feels stuck
the gas pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the engine revs up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch handle can cause the hatch to become stuck or difficult to open, which can lead to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear hatch handle breaks or detaches from the vehicle
the hatch becomes stuck or difficult to open
the release button melts or becomes stuck
the hatch handle garnish falls off
and the wires hang loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch release button can cause the hatch to become stuck or difficult to open, which can lead to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The release button melts or becomes stuck
the button cover falls off
and the wires hang loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch hinge can cause the hatch to become stuck or difficult to open, which can lead to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The top hinges need to be replaced
and the hatch becomes stuck or difficult to open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden crack of the windshield can cause a distraction while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The windshield develops a crack without any apparent impact or cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of the bumper lip can cause a distraction while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear right lip of the bumper falls off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust spots on the lift gate and door frame can lead to structural weakness and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Rust spots appear on the lift gate and front passenger side door frame.
